article.description: Ashley Gayle had a career-high 14 points along with 10 rebounds and six blocks to help Texas (No. 21 ESPN/USA Today, No. 17 AP) beat Texas Southern 91-42 Sunday.
article.headline: Gayle has 14 points, 10 rebounds, six blocks as Texas rolls
article.linkText: Gayle's near triple-double leads No. 21 Texas
article.story:
AUSTIN, Texas -- Ashley Gayle had a career-high 14 points along with 10 rebounds and six blocks to help Texas (No. 21 ESPN/USA Today, No. 17 AP) beat Texas Southern 91-42 Sunday.

Earnesia Williams scored 15 points for the Longhorns (7-3), who got coach Gail Goestenkors her 50th win at Texas since being hired away from Duke in 2007.

Jasmine Payne scored 22 points for Texas Southern (2-7) on 10 for 15 shooting.

Cokie Reed added 12 points for Texas, Kathleen Nash had 11, and Brittainey Raven added 10.
